	<h1> From space power systems to ground-based applications for thermoelectric waste heat recovery </h1>
	
	
	<p>Major energy-saving and CO<sub>2</sub> reducing solutions need to be developed and implemented within the next decade. </p>
	<p>In  the energy and  transportation sectors, well over half of the energy  is discharged as thermal losses to the atmosphere or to cooling systems. Wasted heat is equivalent to at least 2.5 billion barrels of oil per year in the European Union alone. </p>
    <p>       
